    flipkart file

commit 0d40cb6af4865623dac070cebb5ef3922ffa6ecc
Author: root <root@ip-172-31-29-147.ec2.internal>
Date:   Thu Feb 19 05:58:34 2026 +0000

    amazon file
[root@ip-172-31-29-147 mygitfolder]# 


Now the author has been changed for the latest commit

previously we have changed the author name

Now can we able to change the commit message -------> yes

* git git commit --amend --m "this is my new message"       -----------------> command to change message for the latest commit only
here in above command we dont need to mention file name by-defult it will take the latest commit

By using Revert Command we can do delete any particular commit like below

* git update-ref -d HEAD      --------------------------> command to delete all commits what we have done, but files shouldnot get deleted
[root@ip-172-31-29-147 mygitfolder]# git update-ref -d HEAD
[root@ip-172-31-29-147 mygitfolder]# git log
fatal: your current branch 'master' does not have any commits yet
[root@ip-172-31-29-147 mygitfolder]# 

[root@ip-172-31-29-147 mygitfolder]# git status
On branch master

No commits yet

Changes to be committed:
  (use "git rm --cached <file>..." to unstage)
        new file:   amazon
        new file:   flipkart
        new file:   myntra

[root@ip-172-31-29-147 mygitfolder]# 

Now files are in stagging area

[root@ip-172-31-29-147 mygitfolder]# git commit -m "dev1 created amozon file" amazon
[master (root-commit) 4001434] dev1 created amozon file
 1 file changed, 0 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)
 create mode 100644 amazon
[root@ip-172-31-29-147 mygitfolder]# git commit -m "dev2 created flipkart file" flipkart
[master 7578d14] dev2 created flipkart file
 1 file changed, 0 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)
 create mode 100644 flipkart
[root@ip-172-31-29-147 mygitfolder]# git commit -m "dev2 created myntra file" myntra
[master f60ed34] dev2 created myntra file
 1 file changed, 0 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)
 create mode 100644 myntra
[root@ip-172-31-29-147 mygitfolder]#


REVERT means doing changes everything for a particular commit

[root@ip-172-31-29-147 mygitfolder]# git log
commit f60ed34d02eecfcffd8ee804ce855becda0f2348 (HEAD -> master)
Author: pranay <gorantlapranay8@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Feb 19 06:27:43 2026 +0000

    dev2 created myntra file

commit 7578d1435db235abafe7abedba48c5f702a45f07
Author: pranay <gorantlapranay8@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Feb 19 06:27:29 2026 +0000

    dev2 created flipkart file

commit 40014342954fd1a9553c90b366be0071c394a71d
Author: pranay <gorantlapranay8@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Feb 19 06:26:54 2026 +0000

    dev1 created amozon file
[root@ip-172-31-29-147 mygitfolder]# 

[root@ip-172-31-29-147 mygitfolder]# git revert 7578d1435db235abafe7abedba48c5f702a45f07
After giving the above command one file will be open 

no need to made any changes there just do save and continue

:wq

[root@ip-172-31-29-147 mygitfolder]# git log
commit 5244e487b8ae895d8fb569bf371432382e886a25 (HEAD -> master)
Author: pranay <gorantlapranay8@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Feb 19 06:29:39 2026 +0000

    Revert "dev2 created flipkart file"
    
    This reverts commit 7578d1435db235abafe7abedba48c5f702a45f07.


GITHUB
==============

[root@ip-172-31-29-147 mygitfolder]# git branch      -----------------------> command to view on which branch we are in and also to view list of branches
* master -----------------> this is the default branch
[root@ip-172-31-29-147 mygitfolder]# 

GIT MERGE --------------> means to get the changes from one branch to another branch

